{
    "componentChunkName": "component---src-templates-post-template-js",
    "path": "/burn-it-all-down",
    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It was a dark room, except for the west wall. It was illuminated by four panels, two red, a blue, and a green. There were buttons below each of the panels. When pressed, the panel (and adjacent panels) switched their colors: red became blue, blue became green, and green became red. We needed to turn all of these panels red in order to pass."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{"style":"text-align: center; width: 100%"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n    "},{"type":"element","tagName":"iframe","properties":{"width":500,"height":250,"style":"border: solid 1px grey; border-radius: 6px;","src":"https://thbrown.github.io/escape-room-windows"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This was one of the more interesting puzzles we encountered when doing a recent escape room. We ended up using a \"skip puzzle\" ability we earned on this because it's hard to think when you have single-digit number of minutes remaining to escape and when there are 3 other people in the room also pressing the buttons while you are trying to think. However, this puzzle seemed like something that would be interesting to ponder, so when I got home I had chat GPT code it up. It did a perfect job. I went from idea to code to deployed app all in ~5 min. I could have done it myself in maybe 60 min."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Turns out, it's not that difficult to solve once you think about it for a bit (without all the pressure). What might be more interesting is generalizing the puzzle to a second dimension. Chat GPT struggled to code this by itself, but between the LLM and some good old-fashioned manual software engineering, we now have a new version of the escape room game. This iteration also includes some nifty icons for the color-vision impaired."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"burn-it-all-down","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#burn-it-all-down","ariaLabel":"burn it all down permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Burn it all down"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"With this 2D puzzle, your goal, like before, is to turn everything to red fire, hence the title: \"Burn it All Down\"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{"style":"text-align: center; width: 100%"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n    "},{"type":"element","tagName":"iframe","properties":{"width":200,"height":200,"style":"border: solid 1px grey; border-radius: 6px;","src":"https://burn-it-all-down.endlesswips.com/?colors=GqCA&width=3&height=3"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I found this puzzle pretty tricky, but after figuring out a few moves I think I can now solve any random 3x3 tile puzzles in less than a minute. Here's what I figured out..."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"easy-case","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#easy-case","ariaLabel":"easy case permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Easy Case"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It's clear that if you get a homogenous tile grid (even if it's not red), victory is straight-forward. Clicking the middle will change the color of all the tiles until you get to the color you want (red)."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"refreshable-iframe","properties":{"width":200,"height":200,"style":"border: solid 1px grey; border-radius: 6px;","src":"https://burn-it-all-down.endlesswips.com/?colors=VVVA&width=3&height=3","refreshable":"true"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"refreshable-iframe","properties":{},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Note that it might take either one (in the case of starting with green) or two clicks (for blue) to get a grid full of red. This maybe-one-click maybe-two-click behavior sometimes appears in the steps below and is noted by a (x2?) symbol."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"So, the strategy is to make all the outside tiles the same color - any color - then finish up the middle tile last."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Tiles on the outside can either be edges or corners. Here is how to solve both types."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"edge-tiles","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#edge-tiles","ariaLabel":"edge tiles permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Edge Tiles"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In this case, we need to change the incorrect edge tile."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"refreshable-iframe","properties":{"width":200,"height":200,"style":"border: solid 1px grey; border-radius: 6px;","src":"https://burn-it-all-down.endlesswips.com/?colors=VFVA&width=3&height=3","refreshable":"true"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"refreshable-iframe","properties":{},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We click (in any order):"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ol","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The incorrect tile, 2 times"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"One non-middle tile adjacent to the incorrect tile, 1 time\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In this case, the one right "},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"above"}]},{"type":"text","value":" the incorrect tile"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The other non-middle tile adjacent to the incorrect tile, 1 time\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In this case, the one right "},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"below"}]},{"type":"text","value":" the incorrect tile"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Notice that this move also changes the center tile. That's okay - we'll fix that at the end."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"corner-tiles","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#corner-tiles","ariaLabel":"corner tiles permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Corner Tiles"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In this case, we need to change everything except the incorrect corner tile."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"refreshable-iframe","properties":{"width":200,"height":200,"style":"border: solid 1px grey; border-radius: 6px;","src":"https://burn-it-all-down.endlesswips.com/?colors=gAAA&width=3&height=3","refreshable":"true"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"refreshable-iframe","properties":{},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We click (in any order):"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ol","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The tile catty-corner to the bad tile, 2 times\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In this case, the tile farthest from the bad tile, the bottom right (SE tile)"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"One edge tile adjacent to the catty-corner tile\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In this case, the tile above the catty-corner tile, the middle right (E tile)"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The other edge tile adjacent to the catty-corner tile\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In this case, the tile to the left of the catty-corner tile, the middle bottom (S tile)"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Sometimes - (x2?). In this example, you have to do the steps two time: once to turn all the other squares blue, and a second time to turn them green to match the original corner."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"radial-symmetry","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#radial-symmetry","ariaLabel":"radial symmetry permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Radial Symmetry"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Once you've used the moves above to ensure that all the edges and corners are set, we can handle the middle. Unless you've already won. There's a 1 in 3 chance of automatic victory, so your odds aren't too bad!"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Lets assume you haven't won and instead you have a pretty wreath with green on the outside and a pesky red tile in the middle."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"refreshable-iframe","properties":{"width":200,"height":200,"style":"border: solid 1px grey; border-radius: 6px;","src":"https://burn-it-all-down.endlesswips.com/?colors=qiqA&width=3&height=3","refreshable":"true"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"refreshable-iframe","properties":{},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We need to turn this into a checkerboard before we can solve this."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Click all the edge tiles (in any order):"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ol","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"North tile"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"East tile"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"South tile"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"West tile"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Sometimes - (x2?)\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The first time you do these moves, it will either turn the game into a checkerboard OR a cross."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The second time you do these moves it will turn into whatever it didn't turn into the first time."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We want the checkerboard."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"refreshable-iframe","properties":{"width":200,"height":200,"style":"border: solid 1px grey; border-radius: 6px;","src":"https://burn-it-all-down.endlesswips.com/?colors=ZmZA&width=3&height=3","refreshable":"true"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"refreshable-iframe","properties":{},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To solve a checkerboard, just click all the corner tiles:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ol","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"NW tile"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"NE tile"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"SE tile"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"SW tile"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Sometimes - (x2?) Remember you may need to do this twice."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Huzzah! You win!"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"impossible-puzzles","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#impossible-puzzles","ariaLabel":"impossible puzzles permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Impossible Puzzles"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"After experimenting with a few different tile heights and widths, it became pretty clear that not all puzzles are solvable. The most obvious example is a 1x2 or 2x1 grid in which 